### Erroneous Code for Reference
```java
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String variable;
        System.out.println(variable);
    }
}
```

**Errors in the Erroneous Code:**
1. `variable` is declared but not initialized.
2. The variable is not assigned a value, so it is undefined.
3. The code will result in a compilation error due to an undeclared variable.

**Corrected Code:**
```java
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String variable = "Hello world";
        System.out.println(variable);
    }
}
```

